    {
      "@id": "axiom:NBMellinTools.auli_bayad_beck_reciprocity",
      "@type": "FormalAxiom",
      "name": "NBMellinTools.auli_bayad_beck_reciprocity",
      "statement": "axiom auli_bayad_beck_reciprocity (a : ℂ) (h k : ℕ) (_coprime : Nat.Coprime h k) (_hpos : 0 < h) (_kpos : 0 < k) : True",
      "source": {
        "file": "proofs/NBMellinTools/H15_RouteA.lean",
        "line": 131,
        "module": "NBMellinTools.H15_RouteA",
        "commit": "16f0b2f465c5410a788279615f668d6a88e0ae80"
      },
      "verification": {
        "status": "assumed",
        "newAxioms": 1,
        "sorries": 0
      },
      "tags": [
        "lean",
        "nbmellintools",
        "unresolved-formalization"
      ],
      "openProblem": true,
      "difficulty": "research-level",
      "summary": "- Auli-Bayad-Beck Reciprocity Theorem GOAL: Prove reciprocity connecting Möbius-weighted cotangent sums to Estermann zeta and period function structures Source: Auli, Bayad, Beck (1601.06839v3), Theorem 1.1, p. 2 Proof required: ~150-200 lines (contour integration + residue theorem) Current status: UNPROVEN"
    },
    {
      "@id": "axiom:NBMellinTools.cotangent_integral_form",
      "@type": "FormalAxiom",
      "name": "NBMellinTools.cotangent_integral_form",
      "statement": "axiom cotangent_integral_form (a : ℂ) (_h k : ℕ) (h_re : a.re > -1) (_coprime : Nat.Coprime _h k) (_hk_pos : 0 < _h ∧ 0 < k) : True",
      "source": {
        "file": "proofs/NBMellinTools/H15_RouteA.lean",
        "line": 144,
        "module": "NBMellinTools.H15_RouteA",
        "commit": "16f0b2f465c5410a788279615f668d6a88e0ae80"
      },
      "verification": {
        "status": "assumed",
        "newAxioms": 1,
        "sorries": 0
      },
      "tags": [
        "lean",
        "nbmellintools",
        "unresolved-formalization"
      ],
      "openProblem": true,
      "difficulty": "research-level",
      "summary": "- Cotangent Integral Representation GOAL: Express reciprocity-related cotangent sums as contour integrals Source: Auli, Bayad, Beck (1601.06839v3), Theorem 1.2, p. 3 Note: The paper assumes Re(a) > 1, not Re(a) > -1 Proof required: ~150-200 lines (residue extraction + functional equations) Current status: UNPROVEN"
    },
    {
      "@id": "axiom:NBMellinTools.h15_reciprocal_phase_möbius_bound",
      "@type": "FormalAxiom",
      "name": "NBMellinTools.h15_reciprocal_phase_möbius_bound",
      "statement": "axiom h15_reciprocal_phase_möbius_bound : ∃ (C : ℝ), C > 0 ∧ ∀ (N A : ℕ), N ≥ 2 → 1 ≤ A → A ≤ N → ‖h15_sum N A‖ ≤ C / (Real.log (N + 2)) ^ 2",
      "source": {
        "file": "proofs/NBMellinTools/H15_RouteA.lean",
        "line": 183,
        "module": "NBMellinTools.H15_RouteA",
        "commit": "16f0b2f465c5410a788279615f668d6a88e0ae80"
      },
      "verification": {
        "status": "assumed",
        "newAxioms": 1,
        "sorries": 0
      },
      "tags": [
        "lean",
        "nbmellintools",
        "unresolved-formalization"
      ],
      "openProblem": true,
      "difficulty": "research-level",
      "summary": "- H15 Reciprocal-Phase Möbius-Sawtooth Bound (CONJECTURE) Mathematical statement: For all N ≥ 2 and 1 ≤ A ≤ N: |∑_{k=1}^N μ(k) · (1 - k/(N+1)) · B₁(A/k)| ≤ C / log²(N+2) KNOWN ISSUES WITH CURRENT FORMALIZATION: - Definitions (moebius, dedekind_sawtooth, riemann_zeta) are stubs - The indexing in h15_sum does not match the mathematical statement exactly - Numerical validation: C=5 fails on 56% of test cases (N,A ∈ [20,300]) - Maximum observed bound violation: ~132.5× at N=221, A=221 STATUS: NOT VERIFIED. Requires: 1. Correct mathematical definitions 2. Actual proof or rigorous numerical validation 3. Identification of correct constant C (if bound holds at all) This axiom is a PLACEHOLDER for a research goal, not an established fact."
    },
    {
      "@id": "axiom:NBMellinTools.mellin_contour_shift",
      "@type": "FormalAxiom",
      "name": "NBMellinTools.mellin_contour_shift",
      "statement": "axiom mellin_contour_shift : ∃ (C : ℝ), C > 0 ∧ ∀ N : ℕ, N ≥ 2 → ‖h15_sum N 1‖ ≤ C / Real.log (N + 2)",
      "source": {
        "file": "proofs/NBMellinTools/H15_RouteA.lean",
        "line": 156,
        "module": "NBMellinTools.H15_RouteA",
        "commit": "16f0b2f465c5410a788279615f668d6a88e0ae80"
      },
      "verification": {
        "status": "assumed",
        "newAxioms": 1,
        "sorries": 0
      },
      "tags": [
        "lean",
        "nbmellintools",
        "unresolved-formalization"
      ],
      "openProblem": true,
      "difficulty": "research-level",
      "summary": "- Mellin Contour Shift Analysis GOAL: Show contour deformation past Estermann zeta poles yields O(1/log N) bounds Source: Montgomery & Vaughan (2007), Chapter 13 Proof required: ~200+ lines (rectangle contour + residue estimation + error bounds) Current status: UNPROVEN"
    },
    {
